Set env PERL5LIB for your target machine.

Assuming your sysroot/binary root is /path/to/myroot on the target
machine, your perl binary will be under the /path/to/myroot/usr/bin/
directory. With this assumption, I will add the following line to
$HOME/.profile for running perl.

    export PERL5LIB=/path/to/myroot/lib/perl5/5.40.2:/path/to/myroot/usr/lib/perl5/site_perl/5.40.2

Without setting PERL5LIB, perl may not find installed modules.
